<TITLE> WDB official suspended for negligence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)Sunamganj's executive engineer of Bangladesh Water Development Board has been temporarily dismissed on charges of not initiating adequate measures to lessen flood impacts in the Haor areas. A press release on Friday, signed by Mohammed Saifullah, public relations officer of the water resources ministry, also said that the ministry has decided to take legal steps against guilty persons after investigation. Local government representatives have said that 34 haors out of 37 had gone under water in Sunamganj since the beginning of April due to onrush of water from the upper catchments of the rivers. They claimed that about 1.5 lakh hectares of Boro crops have gone under water as most of the protection dams collapsed due to the irregularities of BWDB. Most of the haors in Kishoreganj and Netrakona have also gone under water. bdne
